1
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:33,379
(Previously)
Our family's bloodline is unique.

2
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:35,180
You must use the Dragonblood manual.

3
00:00:35,270 --> 00:00:37,800
But your current bloodline concentration
isn't strong enough.

4
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:38,620
It's alright.

5
00:00:38,650 --> 00:00:40,349
Even if I can't become
a Dragonblood Warrior,

6
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:42,190
I'll still find a way to grow stronger.

7
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:46,500
Kid, your blood awakened this ring.

8
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:50,060
From now on, you're my magic apprentice.

9
00:00:50,230 --> 00:00:52,570
Linley, you've tamed a magical beast.

10
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:54,589
On behalf of the Ernst Institute,

11
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:56,719
I sincerely invite you to join us.

12
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:57,590
Sir,

13
00:00:58,010 --> 00:00:59,260
it is my honor

14
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:01,460
to become a member
of the Ernst Institute.

15
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:33,640
- Coiling Dragon -

16
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,480
Episode 4
FANSUB: H-DONGHUA™

17
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:46,310
Delia, aren't you joining
the competition either?

18
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:49,530
Not interested.

19
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:59,030
Welcome, teachers and students,
to the first-year magic tournament.

20
00:02:59,330 --> 00:03:01,969
Today, the top two first-year
students will be decided.

21
00:03:01,970 --> 00:03:04,110
Please look forward to it.

22
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:06,339
First match, Reno Dunstan

23
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:09,460
(Reno Dunstan)
from the fire-element magic academy.

24
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:12,179
Reno!

25
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:14,680
Isn't that the little monster
from the fire-element magic academy?

26
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,939
Yeah, that's him.

27
00:03:15,940 --> 00:03:17,519
He completed rank-one mage training

28
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,620
while on his way to the academy.

29
00:03:19,980 --> 00:03:21,179
Amazing.

30
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:24,169
And his opponent,
Leto from the water-element magic academy.

31
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:27,850
Leto!

32
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:30,780
A rank-one mage,

33
00:03:31,060 --> 00:03:33,780
although they possess
preliminary magical power,

34
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:36,640
it remains disordered and chaotic,

35
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:39,660
making spellcasting unstable.

36
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:42,020
A rank-two mage

37
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:46,210
gradually forms an orderly circulation
of magical power within the body,

38
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:49,540
allowing stable control of minor spells.

39
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,710
As for a rank-three mage,

40
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:53,549
they must use mental strength

41
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:57,519
to refine the magical power
within their body into a magic vortex.

42
00:03:57,520 --> 00:04:01,420
From ranks four to six,
mental strength condenses into stars.

43
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:05,040
Above rank seven,
those stars form a star chart.

44
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:08,129
You are currently at the rank-two level.

45
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:09,849
Follow my instructions

46
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:12,320
and strive
to break through to rank three.

47
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:22,739
How is that possible?

48
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:26,090
Two minutes and thirty seconds.
Reno Dunstan wins.

49
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:28,669
Reno!

50
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:29,419
Thank you.

51
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:31,179
Reno!

52
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:32,059
Thank you.

53
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:35,900
Reno!

54
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:39,019
As expected of a genius battle mage.

55
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:41,820
The freshman championship
is definitely yours.

56
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,039
Obviously.

57
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,750
Too bad Linley isn't here
to see my shining moment.

58
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:49,800
Showing off again.

59
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:52,740
He's just some small fry.

60
00:04:55,520 --> 00:05:00,240
(Promotion Round Day Two)

61
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,920
(Promotion Round Day Three)

62
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:13,799
(Top Eight of the Promotion Round)

63
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:16,839
(Top Four of the Promotion Round)

64
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,920
(Final Match)

65
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:21,520
(Reno Rank-One Flame Mage VS
Rand ?-Rank Flame Mage)

66
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:44,280
Linley,

67
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,330
if you want to master
rank-three magic power control,

68
00:05:47,540 --> 00:05:50,880
being too impatient is a major taboo.

69
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:52,560
Grandpa Delin,

70
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,250
you're right.

71
00:06:01,780 --> 00:06:04,969
The situation was extremely
dangerous then. His attacks kept coming.

72
00:06:04,970 --> 00:06:07,200
I pretended to retreat,
and he pressed forward.

73
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,160
I turned around

74
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:11,090
and ended the fight
with a single Fireball.

75
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:14,300
From what I've observed,

76
00:06:14,390 --> 00:06:16,850
Rand is already a rank-two mage.

77
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,150
Rand,

78
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:21,600
just looking at that arrogant face
of his annoys me.

79
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,560
Reno will be fine.

80
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:24,920
Of course.

81
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:26,950
Rand is in the same class as me.

82
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:29,740
His rank-two elemental affinity
really is better.

83
00:06:29,970 --> 00:06:31,950
But I'm a genius mage.

84
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:35,700
My mental strength is exceptionally high,
and my control over magic is far superior to his.

85
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,170
I'm back.

86
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:43,970
Linley is back!

87
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:47,429
Seriously, you push yourself
too hard every day.

88
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,170
You need to relax.

89
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:51,730
Exactly. You need a balance
between work and rest.

90
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:58,840
I'm alright.

91
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,440
Go for it, Reno.

92
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:05,630
Linley's family lacks resources.

93
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:08,120
It wasn't easy for him
to become a rank-two mage.

94
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,410
From now on, we should help him more.

95
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,790
Look how exhausted he's been lately.

96
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:14,500
Reno,

97
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,640
you have to win
the championship tomorrow!

98
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:19,130
Win the championship...

99
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,580
Win the championship...

100
00:07:36,510 --> 00:07:40,510
Reno! The championship is ours!

101
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:44,499
Rand number one! Unstoppable!

102
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:49,010
The final match of the Ernst Institute
first-year magic tournament is about to begin.

103
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,929
The atmosphere here today
is incredibly lively.

104
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:53,619
- I'm sure everyone wants to know
- Reno!

105
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:56,810
- who will claim the grade competition championship.
- The championship is ours!

106
00:07:56,860 --> 00:08:00,520
Next, please welcome both contestants
to give their pre-match declarations.

107
00:08:01,130 --> 00:08:02,139
Today,

108
00:08:02,140 --> 00:08:04,690
my flames will shine across Ernst.

109
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,920
In respect for my worthy opponent,
I will show mercy.

110
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:09,540
But definitely not to you,

111
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,680
Rand.

112
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:14,020
All bark and no bite.

113
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:17,609
Tell your friends to get ready.
In a moment,

114
00:08:17,610 --> 00:08:19,510
they'll be carrying you out of here.

115
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:23,620
Such intense hostility
in their speeches.

116
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:25,259
Now I announce,

117
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:28,580
the final match of the Ernst Institute
first-year magic tournament

118
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:30,890
officially begins now!

119
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,960
Reno, go for it!

120
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:44,479
Such fierce flames.

121
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,950
Even the audience in the front rows
can feel intimidated.

122
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,539
The kid's got some skill.

123
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:52,219
But your luck ends here.

124
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:54,590
Heavenfire Meteor!

125
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:57,059
As expected of Reno,
born into a military family.

126
00:08:57,060 --> 00:08:58,940
His reactions rival those of a warrior.

127
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:00,210
Having fun yet?

128
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:01,860
Now it's my turn.

129
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,809
Take this punch!

130
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:05,080
Naive!

131
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,420
No.

132
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,020
This guy's about to play dirty.

133
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:13,500
An opening.

134
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:17,540
You've fallen for it.

135
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,870
You arrogant brat,

136
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:22,380
taste my power!

137
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,180
Reno!

138
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:42,619
Reno ranked up!

139
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:44,020
Nicely done!

140
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:46,420
Reno broke free from the restraint!

141
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:50,660
What?

142
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:54,970
He actually broke through to become
a rank-two mage in the middle of battle!

143
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:58,500
My turn now.

144
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:00,700
Heavenfire Meteor!

145
00:10:05,260 --> 00:10:08,489
(This kid just broke through,
and he's already this troublesome?)

146
00:10:08,490 --> 00:10:10,070
Earthfire Bind!

147
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,259
This...

148
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:14,340
This is...

149
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:19,579
Now it seems Rand has run into trouble.

150
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:20,899
Awesome!

151
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,829
Rand, pull yourself together!

152
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,300
Rand, go!

153
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,079
I can't break free!

154
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:33,120
Brat, if you've got guts, let me go!

155
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,659
Weren't you enjoying yourself just now?

156
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:37,220
Wait, I surrender!

157
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:40,690
What a surprise.

158
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:42,780
So even you know how to surrender.

159
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:44,110
Then I'll let you off this time.

160
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:48,530
What just happened?

161
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,900
Reno actually released Rand.

162
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,100
Useless fool.

163
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:57,300
- Surrender? Dream on!
- Could Rand really be preparing to surrender?

164
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:02,700
So what if you're a rank-two mage?
I'm a rank-three mage!

165
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,420
Earthfire Spell!

166
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:07,820
No!

167
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:10,180
Reno!

168
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,539
The match is already decided. Stop now!

169
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:18,860
Now you know what I'm capable of, right?

170
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:32,140
Go on, keep talking.

171
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,420
Reno!

172
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:34,899
Reno!

173
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:35,899
How are you?

174
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,940
You despicable coward!

175
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:44,980
What a touching display of brotherhood.

176
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:47,940
But right now,

177
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:52,640
shouldn't the most important thing
be announcing the champion?

178
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,189
Right, host?

179
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:56,130
You fool!

180
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,179
If you've got the nerve,
fight me instead.

181
00:11:58,180 --> 00:11:58,980
Yale.

182
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,800
Now's not the time to act recklessly.

183
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,430
Let's get Reno to the infirmary first.

184
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:03,580
Let's go.

185
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:07,149
That incompetent host

186
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:10,149
actually ran off with the loser.

187
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,610
I hereby announce

188
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:14,180
that the champion
of this year's grade competition is

189
00:12:14,190 --> 00:12:15,609
Rand!

190
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:17,590
Rand number one!

191
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,620
Earth Spike!

192
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:33,140
Spear Formation!

193
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:46,010
You've already gained a basic grasp
of this rank-three spell.

194
00:12:46,380 --> 00:12:49,350
I didn't expect
your progress to be this fast.

195
00:12:49,374 --> 00:13:01,374
(Watch the Latest Donoghue Episodes: www.h-donghua.xyz)

196
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:03,409
Sir,

197
00:13:03,410 --> 00:13:04,579
do you have an appointment?

198
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:05,739
This is infuriating!

199
00:13:05,740 --> 00:13:07,570
That shameless Rand!

200
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,900
Brothers, I'm here! Congratulations...

201
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,730
Reno, your favorite drink is here.

202
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:30,269
Calm down, Reno.

203
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:32,499
If it had been a fair match,
you definitely would've won.

204
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,820
Just treat this as a lesson.

205
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:36,460
That's right.

206
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:37,780
Cheers.

207
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:39,040
Mm, cheers.

208
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,300
Well said.

209
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:46,730
You're making it sound like
losing is better than winning.

210
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,020
You...

211
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:50,509
You're not welcome here.

212
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:51,480
Please leave.

213
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:54,260
No need to get worked up.

214
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:56,250
I just came to check on

215
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,989
my respected opponent's

216
00:13:58,990 --> 00:14:00,560
injuries.

217
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:04,899
Someone like you thinks
you deserve to compete?

218
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:05,730
Enough.

219
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:09,320
And who are you supposed to be?

220
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:11,340
What gives you the right?

221
00:14:11,430 --> 00:14:12,680
If you've got the nerve,

222
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:14,740
hit me.

223
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:17,029
You...

224
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:18,180
Let go of me!

225
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,030
- Do you know who I am?
- Rand!

226
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,259
Put Rand down!

227
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,970
You bumpkin!

228
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:24,520
Put me down!

229
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:35,540
Nicely done!

230
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:38,280
Keep the music going.
Everyone, continue eating.

231
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:39,580
Rand.

232
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:44,620
You...

233
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:48,630
You dare hit me?

234
00:14:49,780 --> 00:14:51,780
Rand, fighting in private
is forbidden here.

235
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:53,920
Linley.

236
00:14:55,250 --> 00:15:00,220
What kind of skill is it for a mage
to fight like a warrior?

237
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:03,620
Come on, let's settle this with magic.

238
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:05,280
Yeah, settle it with magic!

239
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,740
Fine then.

240
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,199
Linley,

241
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,160
ignore him.

242
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:12,750
That guy's already rank three.

243
00:15:13,090 --> 00:15:14,090
Alright.

244
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:16,260
We'll meet in the arena later.

245
00:15:16,710 --> 00:15:20,000
The loser must not only avoid
the winner whenever they meet,

246
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:22,589
but also hand over
one hundred gold coins.

247
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:23,730
What do you say?

248
00:15:26,950 --> 00:15:27,970
Rand,

249
00:15:28,090 --> 00:15:30,299
and you call one hundred
gold coins a wager?

250
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,180
How about this?

251
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:34,710
The loser hands over
ten thousand gold coins instead.

252
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:38,080
Ten thousand gold coins?

253
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:40,660
What, scared now?

254
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:44,670
Rand, the three of us can scrape together
ten thousand gold coins.

255
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,290
Besides, that guy clearly
isn't your match.

256
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:52,540
Fine. Ten thousand gold coins it is.

257
00:15:54,420 --> 00:15:56,070
See you later.

258
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:10,000
I'll make you regret this.

259
00:16:10,024 --> 00:16:38,824
FANSUB: H-DONGHUA™

